<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><listPerson xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><person xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="BRE01" sex="2"><persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><roleName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Miss</roleName><forename xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Charlotte</forename><surname xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Brent</surname><addName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></persName><birth xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1000"><placeName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></birth><death xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1000"/><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/><note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="editorial"> Charlotte is the younger (very attractive) sister 
    of <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="MOR07">Mary Brent/Morgan</persName>, 
    married to <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="MOR06">John Morgan</persName>, friend of Coleridge. 
    <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="COL01">Coleridge</persName> was much taken with Charlotte.   
    The entries coded are to Miss Brent. However there are a few later 
    Brent entries, which might relate to 
    Charlotte, or might be to her father, a Hatton Garden silversmith. However, 
    all these Brent entries are in the company of Morgan, and John Morgan 
    has died before these later entries, which 
    suggests that Morgan and Brent might refer to the 
    two sisters.  They have been coded as such, although the attribution is uncertain.
  
